<p><b>What is Shenpa in Buddhism?</b> The Tibetan word for this is shenpa. It is usually translated “attachment,” but a more descriptive translation might be “hooked.” When shenpa hooks us, we're likely to get stuck. We could call shenpa “that sticky feeling.” It's an everyday experience.</p>
